---
@META
dir: skillsPraut/src/hooks
updated: 2026-04-15
files: 6
stack: TypeScript, Remotion

@EXPORTS
easings.ts: easings — { linear, out, standard, inOutExpo, outBack, outQuart, inOutCubic } + easeOutElastic, easeOutBounce functions
useEnterExit.ts: useEnterExit — reusable enter+exit spring lifecycle (delay, enterDuration, exitDuration)
interpolateColors.ts: interpolateColors — linear hex lerp → "rgb()"
useCountUp.ts: useCountUp — spring-driven numeric count-up
useScaleToFit.ts: useScaleToFit — scale factor reference→actual
useStaggeredAnimation.ts: useStaggeredAnimation — index→progress stagger
useTypewriter.ts: useTypewriter — character-by-character typing

@FUNCTIONS
interpolateColors(t: number, from: string, to: string) → string
  purpose: lerp two #RRGGBB hex colors → rgb(…)
  side-effects: none
useCountUp({from?, to, startFrame?, config?}) → number
  purpose: count-up numeric animation via spring
  side-effects: useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig
useScaleToFit(refWidth?: 1920, refHeight?: 1080) → number
  purpose: CSS scale to fit reference dims into composition dims
  side-effects: useVideoConfig
useStaggeredAnimation({staggerFrames?, startFrame?, config?}) → (index)→number
  purpose: per-index spring progress for staggered reveals
  side-effects: useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig
useTypewriter({fullText, pauseAfter?, charFrames?, pauseSeconds?}) → string
  purpose: typewriter substring at current frame
  side-effects: useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: styles/tokens (springs, timing, frame)
external: remotion (spring, useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig, Easing, interpolate)

@STANDARDS
- All animation hooks depend on useCurrentFrame + useVideoConfig
- Defaults pulled from tokens.springs / tokens.timing
- useCountUp default: springs.smooth
- useStaggeredAnimation default: staggerFrames=12 (timing.fast)
- useTypewriter default: 2 frames per char
- Deterministic per-frame output (no randomness, cacheable)
- easings.ts has 7 bezier curves + 2 easing functions — never use custom cubic-bezier
- useEnterExit returns 0→1→0 progress driven by parent Sequence durationInFrames
---
